<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 30 at 9:03PM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern Blaine
County through 930 PM MDT...
At 902 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles south of Turner, or 36 miles east of Chinook, moving northeast
at 35 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Turner and Hogeland.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...55 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
